00:00:07.900 --> 00:00:10.104 position:10% line:83% align:start
We've secured Professor Kou
Honda.

00:00:12.673 --> 00:00:15.610 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Gasps] Could you repeat that,
Hiruma?

00:00:15.812 --> 00:00:19.951 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Ichiro Hiruma) Professor Honda.</i>
 <i>The man responsible for creating</i>
 <i>Akari Hizamaru.</i>

00:00:19.984 --> 00:00:21.753 position:35% line:5% align:start
 <i>Ludicrous!</i>

00:00:23.656 --> 00:00:27.028 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Luke Snorresson) How can that</i>
 <i>be? Professor Honda was reported</i>
 <i>dead twenty years ago!</i>

00:00:27.061 --> 00:00:29.731 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Ichiro Hiruma) I just talked to</i>
 <i>him on the phone myself.</i>

00:00:30.099 --> 00:00:31.868 position:19% line:89% align:start
He seemed fine to me.

00:00:32.135 --> 00:00:34.972 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Gulping]

00:00:35.005 --> 00:00:37.175 position:30% line:83% align:start
That's rather
fortuitous news.

00:00:37.776 --> 00:00:43.318 position:21% line:71% align:start
(Chinese Leader) His
extraordinary talent and
research aren't lost to humanity
after all.

00:00:44.819 --> 00:00:50.394 position:10% line:77% align:start
We must invite him to U-NASA
posthaste. We can work with him
together toward our shared goal.

00:00:50.428 --> 00:00:54.233 position:7% line:77% align:start
With his knowledge we stand a
chance of finding a cure for
the virus!

00:00:56.202 --> 00:00:57.238 position:44% line:89% align:start
No.

00:00:57.271 --> 00:00:58.672 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Gulps]

00:01:01.410 --> 00:01:04.915 position:7% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Hiruma) Japan's technological</i>
 <i>infrastructure is more than</i>
 <i>adequate to make proper use of</i>
 <i>Professor Honda's research.</i>

00:01:04.948 --> 00:01:09.955 position:10% line:83% align:start
For results, of course, that
benefit the entire human race.

00:01:09.989 --> 00:01:12.225 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Chinese Leader) But wait!</i>
 <i>You haven't always...</i>

00:01:12.726 --> 00:01:14.295 position:35% line:89% align:start
Trust me!

00:01:15.364 --> 00:01:16.865 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:02:52.602 --> 00:03:00.647 position:7% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Narrator) Meanwhile on Mars,</i>
 <i>Shokichi Komachi has met his</i>
 <i>match as Squad Four's covert</i>
 <i>operation takes its toll.</i>

00:03:00.681 --> 00:03:07.389 position:10% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Narrator) Captain Komachi's</i>
 <i>only hope is Squad Three,</i>
 <i>Squad Four's former partner</i>
 <i>and ally.</i>

00:03:07.423 --> 00:03:10.293 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Narrator) All eyes are now on</i>
 <i>Liu and Asimov.</i>

00:03:10.327 --> 00:03:15.568 position:13% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Narrator) As the struggle</i>
 <i>between the two Squad leaders</i>
 <i>erupts into an all-out battle of</i>
 <i>wills.</i>

00:03:16.235 --> 00:03:17.270 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Screams]

00:03:17.303 --> 00:03:18.339 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Groans]

00:03:20.007 --> 00:03:21.209 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:03:27.385 --> 00:03:29.153 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:03:31.190 --> 00:03:35.029 position:13% line:71% align:start
(Liu) You've made a fatal
mistake in assuming we are all
just helpless engineers without
our weapons.

00:03:38.133 --> 00:03:39.602 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Liu) What's the matter?</i>

00:03:40.069 --> 00:03:41.605 position:16% line:89% align:start
Out of rousing speeches?

00:03:41.638 --> 00:03:44.476 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:03:47.279 --> 00:03:49.416 position:5% line:89% align:start
It seems you've lost a few men.

00:03:49.449 --> 00:03:53.222 position:5% line:77% align:start
Bao and Borgijin, now that we're
in control, take Hong into Annex
One.

00:03:53.255 --> 00:03:54.890 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Bao) Yes, General Liu.</i>

00:03:57.360 --> 00:03:58.362 position:21% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Borgijin) Let's go.</i>

00:03:59.029 --> 00:04:02.167 position:5% line:89% align:start
Ah, okay. Wait for me, Borgijin.

00:04:03.569 --> 00:04:07.409 position:10% line:77% align:start
If an alliance isn't to your
liking, perhaps neutrality's
more your speed?

00:04:07.442 --> 00:04:12.482 position:13% line:77% align:start
Stay neutral? You must be
joking. But you've got a
terrible sense of humor.

00:04:16.988 --> 00:04:19.926 position:10% line:77% align:start
 <i>(President Smiles) I saw the</i>
 <i>hieroglyphs from the Martian</i>
 <i>pyramid.</i>

00:04:20.193 --> 00:04:23.330 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(President Smiles) We are by no</i>
 <i>means in a position to</i>
 <i>criticize.</i>

00:04:23.364 --> 00:04:28.104 position:13% line:71% align:start
 <i>(President Smiles) But it</i>
 <i>appears the Chinese Squad has</i>
 <i>taken its own goals to the</i>
 <i>extreme.</i>

00:04:28.639 --> 00:04:34.213 position:10% line:77% align:start
They seem confident in their
ability to take on every other
Squad, I'll give them that much.

00:04:34.246 --> 00:04:38.152 position:7% line:83% align:start
Tell me this, Asimov, how was
your mission in the pyramid?

00:04:38.519 --> 00:04:41.223 position:10% line:83% align:start
Good news, we found what we
wanted.

00:04:41.256 --> 00:04:45.162 position:13% line:83% align:start
Excellent. For the moment,
Russia now has the upper hand.

00:04:45.696 --> 00:04:51.505 position:7% line:71% align:start
 <i>(President Smiles) Japan has a</i>
 <i>powerful card in its deck, but</i>
 <i>that just means we need to</i>
 <i>reconsider our alliances</i> .

00:04:51.538 --> 00:04:53.775 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>(President Smiles) For now, we</i>
 <i>stick to the plan.</i>

00:04:53.808 --> 00:04:55.009 position:33% line:89% align:start
Understood.

00:04:56.612 --> 00:04:59.616 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Sylvester) We'll do everything</i>
 <i>we can to help create a vaccine</i>
 <i>for Earth.</i>

00:05:00.383 --> 00:05:06.559 position:10% line:71% align:start
So that's the famous Fa jin
strike I've heard so much about.
That was an unprecedented first,
I must say.

00:05:07.360 --> 00:05:09.597 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Sylvester) My insides are still</i>
 <i>vibrating.</i>

00:05:09.630 --> 00:05:12.735 position:7% line:83% align:start
I would go so far as to say I
can still feel its effects.

00:05:12.768 --> 00:05:17.642 position:10% line:71% align:start
Yet I can't help but wonder.
Does it really take a person
decades to learn that one
powerful move?

00:05:17.675 --> 00:05:22.449 position:7% line:77% align:start
That doesn't seem like a wise
use of time. After all, a
measly poke won't win a fight!

00:05:22.716 --> 00:05:23.683 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:05:24.117 --> 00:05:25.653 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:05:26.187 --> 00:05:27.556 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Groans]

00:05:29.792 --> 00:05:35.701 position:10% line:5% align:start
 <i>(Liu) Incredible! He took a</i>
 <i>solid punch to his internal</i>
 <i>organs and he's able to stage an</i>
 <i>attack!</i>

00:05:36.301 --> 00:05:38.572 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:05:38.605 --> 00:05:40.307 position:5% line:89% align:start
Now I've got you.

00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:44.280 position:7% line:83% align:start
And I won't let you go. You'll
die slowly from this poison.

00:05:44.313 --> 00:05:46.616 position:13% line:89% align:start
I don't think so. [Grunts]

00:05:50.556 --> 00:05:56.397 position:5% line:77% align:start
Your tentacle grip on my arms is
useless. And now I'm going to
crush your torso into slop.

00:05:56.430 --> 00:05:59.234 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Sylvester) Let's see you</i>
 <i>regenerate after that!</i>

00:05:59.702 --> 00:06:02.271 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Screams]

00:06:03.674 --> 00:06:05.777 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>(Liu) Damn this Crab bastard!</i>

00:06:08.147 --> 00:06:11.351 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>(Liu) The best he can hope for</i>
 <i>here is that we both die. Give</i>
 <i>it up! You're a soldier after</i>
 <i>all.</i>

00:06:13.354 --> 00:06:14.656 position:35% line:89% align:start
Watch out!

00:06:14.690 --> 00:06:17.594 position:5% line:83% align:start
He'll be fine, Ivan. Don't
forget your assignment.

00:06:19.663 --> 00:06:22.835 position:10% line:83% align:start
They should've ambushed him,
there's no stopping him now.

00:06:23.736 --> 00:06:26.773 position:7% line:83% align:start
(Aaron) If you insist on going
to help him...

00:06:28.309 --> 00:06:30.846 position:5% line:83% align:start
(Aaron) You'll have to kill the
two of us first.

00:06:31.313 --> 00:06:32.281 position:5% line:89% align:start
Idiots.

00:06:33.951 --> 00:06:37.254 position:5% line:5% align:start
 <i>(Jet) Do these two fools have a</i>
 <i>death wish? Or are they waiting</i>
 <i>for something?</i>

00:06:38.390 --> 00:06:39.692 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Gasps]

00:06:42.062 --> 00:06:46.769 position:10% line:71% align:start
Hey! Quit showing off those
nasty tentacles, octopus-man!
While you're at it, cut it with
the poison and let my boss go.

00:06:46.802 --> 00:06:50.307 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) Nobody else gets to</i>
 <i>use their powers either,</i>
 <i>understood?</i>

00:06:51.909 --> 00:06:56.148 position:13% line:77% align:start
For incentive, if you try
anything, I'll light you up with
this missile I found.

00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:58.385 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) Imagine my luck.</i>

00:07:01.089 --> 00:07:04.727 position:7% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) Coming across this</i>
 <i>surface to surface missile and</i>
 <i>launcher conveniently loaded</i>
 <i>inside your exploratory vehicle.</i>

00:07:04.761 --> 00:07:08.600 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) I'm impressed you</i>
 <i>fit all this in the tiny</i>
 <i>cargo hold of the Annex.</i>

00:07:08.633 --> 00:07:11.303 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) But now I understand</i>
 <i>the core of your plan.</i>

00:07:11.337 --> 00:07:15.242 position:13% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) It's not this</i>
 <i>missile or any other weapon.</i>
 <i>It's that radio tower.</i>

00:07:15.275 --> 00:07:19.248 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) Mr. Super Antenna</i>
 <i>over there is what's causing</i>
 <i>the communications disruption.</i>

00:07:19.281 --> 00:07:21.284 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) What happens if he</i>
 <i>goes down?</i>

00:07:22.987 --> 00:07:25.958 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) If we call Earth and</i>
 <i>tell them all the nasty things</i>
 <i>you've been up to,</i>

00:07:25.992 --> 00:07:29.830 position:10% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) your bosses will</i>
 <i>disavow you so fast your head</i>
 <i>will spin.</i>

00:07:29.863 --> 00:07:33.268 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) "This was all their</i>
 <i>idea, not ours." That's what</i>
 <i>they'll say.</i>

00:07:33.301 --> 00:07:38.609 position:7% line:71% align:start
Now I'm sure you don't want to
die. I mean, you must have
families waiting for you back
home.

00:07:39.577 --> 00:07:41.313 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Sighs]

00:07:42.782 --> 00:07:44.317 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hah.

00:07:46.188 --> 00:07:50.660 position:21% line:71% align:start
General Liu turned off his
poison. In good faith, I'll take
off my mask and won't use my
power.

00:07:50.693 --> 00:07:56.468 position:7% line:71% align:start
Keep talking and we'll listen.
Since you've been blabbing on
like that, you must want to
negotiate, am I right?

00:07:56.501 --> 00:07:58.637 position:21% line:89% align:start
Well, if you insist.

00:08:00.907 --> 00:08:04.913 position:5% line:71% align:start
We cooperated with you for Plan
Delta. Now we want exclusive
rights to the Annex lab to
develop an anti-viral cure.

00:08:16.029 --> 00:08:19.534 position:5% line:83% align:start
Here's the deal! We do have some
decency, you know!

00:08:19.567 --> 00:08:24.809 position:5% line:77% align:start
Agree to work for us, and give
up on stealing Officer Davis and
the other Akari guy.

00:08:24.842 --> 00:08:26.811 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) I won't blow the</i>
 <i>tower into pieces.</i>

00:08:28.747 --> 00:08:31.986 position:10% line:71% align:start
And we'll all come up with a
clever story to tell Earth.
Sounds like a pretty fair deal
to me.

00:08:34.890 --> 00:08:35.857 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:08:38.427 --> 00:08:39.930 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) Halt!</i>

00:08:44.937 --> 00:08:50.746 position:5% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Alexander) What are you doing?</i>
 <i>Sorry, sweetheart, but your</i>
 <i>little honey trap isn't going to</i>
 <i>work.</i>

00:08:50.946 --> 00:08:52.347 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Gasps]

00:08:57.454 --> 00:08:58.623 position:35% line:89% align:start
[Screams]

00:09:03.831 --> 00:09:04.999 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:09:06.202 --> 00:09:09.471 position:5% line:83% align:start
Shall we resume our dance? Or is
the poison too much for you?

00:09:09.505 --> 00:09:10.707 position:55% line:83% align:start
You don't look
so well, yourself.

00:09:11.809 --> 00:09:13.711 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Sylvester) Poison doesn't just</i>
 <i>weaken its target.</i>

00:09:15.113 --> 00:09:17.517 position:5% line:77% align:start
You're going to wish you hadn't
interrupted our plan. Xi, kill
him!

00:09:18.518 --> 00:09:19.452 position:5% line:89% align:start
I shall!

00:09:24.493 --> 00:09:25.695 position:72% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:09:25.728 --> 00:09:26.697 position:5% line:89% align:start
Heh!

00:09:31.604 --> 00:09:32.738 position:44% line:89% align:start
Uh!

00:09:33.073 --> 00:09:34.608 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Groans]

00:09:49.997 --> 00:09:51.531 position:5% line:89% align:start
What's happening?

00:09:52.233 --> 00:09:56.672 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's dark. The sky was bright
just a second ago!

00:10:01.246 --> 00:10:09.024 position:21% line:89% align:start
Jo-ji! Jo-ji! Jo-ji!

00:10:14.265 --> 00:10:16.501 position:41% line:89% align:start
Now they come back?

00:10:17.502 --> 00:10:19.838 position:24% line:5% align:start
 <i>Was this their strategy?</i>

00:10:21.207 --> 00:10:26.148 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Terraformars Buzzing]

00:10:28.184 --> 00:10:29.353 position:19% line:89% align:start
They're too damn loud!

00:10:29.386 --> 00:10:33.158 position:5% line:83% align:start
That's not just buzzing. I think
we're hearing laughter!

00:10:33.191 --> 00:10:34.727 position:5% line:89% align:start
What Aaron?

00:10:34.760 --> 00:10:37.130 position:30% line:89% align:start
They're laughing at us.

00:10:37.164 --> 00:10:42.604 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Aaron) They're watching humans</i>
 <i>kill humans. They're laughing at</i>
 <i>our own self destruction!</i>

00:10:43.106 --> 00:10:44.841 position:24% line:89% align:start
Shut the hell up!

00:10:48.080 --> 00:10:50.682 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Terraformars Buzzing]

00:10:50.716 --> 00:10:51.985 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>They're not attacking at once?</i>

00:11:03.701 --> 00:11:04.635 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:11:04.669 --> 00:11:06.071 position:52% line:89% align:start
Michelle, look!

00:11:11.279 --> 00:11:13.682 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Michelle) They're heading for</i>
 <i>the Annex facility!</i>

00:11:15.718 --> 00:11:17.287 position:10% line:89% align:start
The captain, and the others.

00:11:17.321 --> 00:11:19.090 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Akari) What do we do?</i>

00:11:31.908 --> 00:11:33.911 position:44% line:89% align:start
Jo!

00:11:36.114 --> 00:11:38.217 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Akari) It's like they're</i>
 <i>patrolling the area.</i>

00:11:38.951 --> 00:11:41.889 position:13% line:83% align:start
Does this mean their chain of
command is back online?

00:11:42.257 --> 00:11:46.128 position:7% line:77% align:start
We rendezvous with Squad Six.
Just as we had originally
planned.

00:11:46.162 --> 00:11:47.097 position:78% line:89% align:start
Roger!

00:11:52.237 --> 00:11:55.108 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>They must have a leader. Where</i>
 <i>is it?</i>

00:12:02.752 --> 00:12:03.987 position:33% line:5% align:start
 <i>Is that him?</i>

00:12:04.721 --> 00:12:07.225 position:41% line:89% align:start
Jo-jo.

00:12:10.696 --> 00:12:12.732 position:35% line:89% align:start
Is that, a dragonfly?

00:12:12.766 --> 00:12:14.102 position:5% line:89% align:start
A what now?

00:12:14.135 --> 00:12:17.706 position:10% line:83% align:start
It has to be. It has dragonfly
wings on its back.

00:12:18.842 --> 00:12:20.411 position:21% line:89% align:start
The demon dragonfly.

00:12:20.444 --> 00:12:21.279 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>(Sergei) That's not good.</i>

00:12:22.214 --> 00:12:24.350 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's fast. But one of us has
that speed.

00:12:28.989 --> 00:12:30.258 position:5% line:89% align:start
The truck!

00:12:30.291 --> 00:12:31.025 position:5% line:5% align:start
 <i>It's a beast.</i>

00:12:31.059 --> 00:12:32.294 position:38% line:89% align:start
Enough!

00:12:38.035 --> 00:12:39.004 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:12:42.809 --> 00:12:44.078 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:48.351 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:12:49.353 --> 00:12:50.053 position:78% line:89% align:start
Aaron!

00:12:51.355 --> 00:12:54.826 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:12:57.864 --> 00:13:00.001 position:30% line:89% align:start
Aaron! Aaron!

00:13:03.038 --> 00:13:04.140 position:38% line:89% align:start
[Grunts]

00:13:21.364 --> 00:13:23.434 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>Bizarre! They took the bodies!</i>

00:13:23.467 --> 00:13:25.102 position:41% line:89% align:start
Jo-jo!

00:13:41.560 --> 00:13:42.494 position:41% line:89% align:start
Jo-ji!

00:13:44.029 --> 00:13:45.232 position:44% line:89% align:start
Jo!

00:13:45.265 --> 00:13:46.467 position:33% line:89% align:start
Their young?

00:13:48.202 --> 00:13:51.039 position:16% line:5% align:start
 <i>I expected them to have</i>
 <i>offspring, but why aren't any</i>
 <i>adults fighting?</i>

00:13:53.277 --> 00:13:57.315 position:13% line:5% align:start
 <i>Their old leader was very</i>
 <i>competent. But a strong leader</i>
 <i>caused the rest of the horde to</i>
 <i>be too dependent.</i>

00:13:57.349 --> 00:14:00.420 position:5% line:5% align:start
 <i>That's why they weren't ready to</i>
 <i>attack us until now.</i>

00:14:00.820 --> 00:14:05.327 position:7% line:5% align:start
 <i>(Sylvester) And somehow their</i>
 <i>colony recovered in a mere week?</i>
 <i>It's incredible!</i>

00:14:05.361 --> 00:14:06.929 position:38% line:89% align:start
Jo-joji!

00:14:06.962 --> 00:14:08.798 position:5% line:89% align:start
Ju-juji!

00:14:20.382 --> 00:14:22.285 position:33% line:89% align:start
Jo-ji jo-ji!

